    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="573"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 783.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s reply of the 19th
                    ultimo to your dispatch No. 654, of April 3 last, concerning the towing of the
                    disabled French steamship <hi rend="italic">Bretagne</hi> into the port of Bahia
                    by the United States cruiser <hi rend="italic">Chicago</hi>, I inclose for
                    communication to the “Société Générate de Transports Maritimes á Vapeur” at
                    Paris a copy of a letter from the Secretary of the Navy reporting that a copy of
                    your abovementioned dispatch with its accompanying papers had been forwarded to
                    Rear-Admiral W. S. Schley, U. S. N.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">M <persName type="from">Long</persName> to Mr. <persName
                                type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-04-21">
                                <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt
                        of your letter of the 19th instant, inclosing for the information of this
                        Department a copy of a dispatch from the Ambassador of the United States at
                        Paris, inclosing a copy of a letter from the “Société Générale de Transports
                        Maritimes à Vapeur” concerning the towing of the disabled steamship <hi
                            rend="italic">Bretagne</hi> into the port of Bahia by the U. S. S. <hi
                            rend="italic">Chicago.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>A copy of the letter with its inclosure had heen forwarded to Rear-Admiral W.
                        S. Schley.</p>
                    <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John D. Long.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
